```
This ques is all about converting a single linkedlist into a circular linkedlist after rotating the nodes k times.
Lets first understand about the k .
```
Let assume the length of the linked list given is L.
so,there can be 2 possible cases;
1-**When k < L**
Ex: {1,2,3} k=2 Move the list after the 1st node to the front

2-**When k > L**
Ex: {1,2,3} k=5, In this case Move the list after 1 st node to the front.

So, to calculate after rotation of nodes which node to be use as the head of the node we can use the formula
***[ L-k%L ]*** which is valid for both the upr cases .

Now we came to a conclusion that this conde consist of 3 major parts:
* Converting singly Linkedlist to a circular:-
         which means last nodes points toward the head of the link list
* Calculating the length of the Linnkedlist :-
         we can use a pointer `curr` in a while loop in which we will forward the curr pointer till it reaches the end of              the list and every time it moves forward we store it in a `count` variable which give us the length
* Calculating  `k=Count -(k %Count)` 
* Rotate the nodes;

```
Let's understand it visually :-
```

![image](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/7b371609-3a96-4f58-b17d-b7495bb75ca8_1646973846.1428955.jpeg)

![image](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/0044ac8a-f761-45c7-a971-6dedd4c1110c_1646974034.2282662.jpeg)

![image](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/91b1f303-4668-4c32-949b-3066d3b276c0_1646974086.2907307.jpeg)

![image](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/fac99020-40bf-4d3a-9cdb-da5fcca55da0_1646974132.3556378.jpeg)

***SO , LETS CODE IT ***

***JAVA***

```
class Solution {
    public ListNode rotateRight(ListNode head, int k) {
        // Base Condition OR edge case
        if(head == null || head.next == null || k == 0) return head;

        ListNode curr = head; // pointer current
        int count = 1; // here count is length
        while(curr.next != null){ // reach end of list, and have the count
            count++;
            curr = curr.next;
        }
        curr.next = head; // connect last node to head node to make it circular
        k = count - (k % count); // get the length
        while(k--> 0) curr = curr.next; // now move pointer, to the kth node
        head = curr.next; // make the head 
        curr.next = null; // and point that curr to null

        return head;
    }
}
```

