# Approach
![image.png](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/2045c536-b1e2-403e-a7e7-3aff7c040ba4_1692104707.3630223.png)

Main idea is to convert Singly Linked List into a Circular Linked List. 
For that, we traverse till `curr -> next != NULL` which is the last node, and then point it to the head : `curr -> next = head`

Then instead of rotating the list k times, we would rotate it 0 times if k = 5 for length = 5, rotate it once it k = 6 such that, twice if k = 7 and so on. So we count total rotations to be made as `k = k % length`

The pointer currently points to the tail of the SLL which is now connected to the head. We now move it to `k = length - k`


# Complexity
- Time complexity: $$O(n)$$ 

- Space complexity: $$O(1)$$ 

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    ListNode* rotateRight(ListNode* head, int k) {
        if(head == NULL || k == 0 || head->next == NULL)    return head;

        ListNode* curr = head;
        int length = 1;

        while(curr->next != NULL) {
            curr = curr->next;
            length++;
        }

        curr->next = head;
        k = k % length;
        k = length - k;
        while(k--)  curr = curr->next;

        head = curr->next;
        curr->next = NULL;

        return head;
    }
};
```

